  "abstract": "&lt;p&gt;This is an evaluation framework designed to evaluate the ability of large language models in generating hardware assertions. We use natural language prompts, such as those one would see as code comments in assertion files, to produce SystemVerilog assertions. Our framework automatically generates 20k+ prompts targeting the generation of 10 assertions, prompts the LLM to generate 220k+ SystemVerilog assertions, evaluates the correctness of these assertions using simulation-based testing, and summarizes the ability of LLMs in generating assertions across seven different metrics. Our framework is published as&nbsp;&lt;a href=\"https://ieeexplore.ieee.org/document/10458667\" rel=\"nofollow\"&gt;\"(Security) Assertions by Large Language Models\"&lt;/a&gt; at IEEE Transactions on Information Forensics and Security, 2024.&lt;/p&gt;",
